      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Computational Efficiency Tips\n",
        "\n",
        "### Vectorization is Key\n",
        "\n",
        "**Slow (loops)**: Takes ~10 seconds for 100,000 paths\n",
        "```python\n",
        "for path in range(n_paths):\n",
        "    for t in range(n_steps):\n",
        "        r = r + drift + diffusion\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Fast (NumPy)**: Takes ~0.5 seconds\n",
        "```python\n",
        "Z = np.random.standard_normal((n_steps, n_paths))\n",
        "paths = r0 + np.cumsum(drift_term * Z, axis=0)\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### Memory Considerations\n",
        "\n",
        "- **5000 paths × 1000 steps**: ~40 MB (manageable)\n",
        "- **100,000 paths × 1000 steps**: ~800 MB (consider careful)\n",
        "- **1 million paths**: ~8 GB (use batching)\n",
        "\n",
        "For large simulations, consider:\n",
        "```python\n",
        "def price_bonds_batched(n_paths_total, batch_size=10000):\n",
        "    for batch in range(0, n_paths_total, batch_size):\n",
        "        paths = simulate_paths(batch_size)\n",
        "        bond_prices = price_bonds(paths)\n",
        "        accumulate_results(bond_prices)\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Summary\n",
        "\n",
        "✓ Implemented vectorized Dothan model simulator  \n",
        "✓ Generated 5000 interest rate paths  \n",
        "✓ Validated lognormality and moments  \n",
        "✓ Analyzed parameter sensitivity  \n",
        "✓ Optimized for computational efficiency  \n",
        "\n",
        "Next: Use these paths to **price bonds**!"
      ],
      "id": "ae17f6f9"
    }
